Goal:
Build a scalable Fastify + PostgreSQL backend for an MLM (Multi-Level Marketing) platform that sells courses and manages multi-level commission distributions (Self, Global Helping, Spot, Monthly).

The system must handle automatic commission calculation, daily payouts, multi-level eligibility checks, and wallet reconciliation — all in a fault-tolerant, idempotent, and auditable way.

⚙️ Project Overview

We are developing a backend that handles:

User registration & referral tracking (up to 9 levels deep).

Course (package) purchases with validity (in months).

Daily and instant commission calculations.

Dynamic eligibility-based multi-level commission release.

Wallet, ledger, and reconciliation systems for full transparency.

All money movements must be fully auditable, idempotent, and traceable between:

source_user_id → who triggered the earning

receiver_user_id → who earned it

🏗️ Tech Stack

Node.js + Fastify (for performance and modularity)

PostgreSQL (core database)

PgBoss (for async background workers — no Redis required)

TypeScript (for strict typing)

Docker Compose (for Postgres + PgBoss + Fastify container)

Jest (for automated tests)

🧩 Core Features
1️⃣ Users & Referrals

Users can register with a referrer.

Maintain a closure table (user_tree_paths) for up to 9 levels of referrals.

Automatically update referral paths when a user joins.

2️⃣ Packages / Courses

Each package defines:

price

validity_months

self_monthly

global_ids

global_monthly_per_id

recurring_rate_percent

3️⃣ Purchases

When a user purchases a package:

Save purchase with active_until = purchase_date + validity_months

Mark user active until that date.

Trigger the commission generation pipeline asynchronously (via PgBoss job).

4️⃣ Commission Types

Unified four commission types:

Type	Description	Frequency
SELF	Daily credit based on user’s own purchase	Daily
GLOBAL_HELPING	Daily global helping income	Daily
SPOT	One-time direct 5% commission	Immediate
MONTHLY	0.5% recurring monthly income (paid daily)	Daily

Each record must link:

receiver_user_id

source_user_id

purchase_id

commission_type

amount

metadata.level

⚙️ Eligibility

Level-based commissions (1–9 levels) depend on leg business volume.

Rules are stored in commission_rules.

PgBoss background workers recalculate eligibility dynamically.

Pending commissions are released when eligibility is achieved.

🕒 Validity

A user is active if they have at least one valid purchase where
active_until >= CURRENT_DATE.

Before adding any commission to a wallet:

Check if both source and receiver are active.

💰 Wallet & Ledger System

ledger_entries — immutable financial record.

wallet_transactions — mirror wallet-level operations from ledger.

user_balances — cached total wallet balance per user.

Every credit/debit must use an idempotency_key and DB transaction.

🗃️ Database Schema

Cursor should generate models (or Prisma schema) with the following tables:

1. users
2. packages
3. purchases
4. user_tree_paths (closure table)
5. ledger_entries
6. wallet_transactions
7. pending_commissions
8. scheduled_commissions
9. level_eligibility
10. commission_rules
11. user_balances

All definitions as finalized (receiver/source linkage, dynamic validity check, no static source_active_until).

📦 API Endpoints

Create REST routes under /api/v1 with Zod schema validation:

Method	Route	Description
POST	/users/register	Register new user (optional referrer)
POST	/packages	Create new course package (admin)
GET	/packages	List all packages
POST	/purchases	User purchases a package
GET	/users/:id/wallet	Wallet balance + recent ledger
GET	/users/:id/pending	Pending commissions
GET	/users/:id/eligibility	Eligibility snapshot
POST	/admin/release-pending	Admin manual release
GET	/reports/reconciliation	Ledger vs wallet check
⚙️ Commission Logic Implementation
💰 Purchase Flow

When /purchases is called:

Insert purchase record.

Create scheduled SELF + GLOBAL_HELPING commissions.

Credit 5% SPOT to direct referrer.

Schedule 0.5% MONTHLY recurring for referrer.

Traverse up to 9 uplines using user_tree_paths:

If eligible → create commission.

If not → insert into pending_commissions.

All of this runs via a PgBoss job (purchase-commission).

🔁 PgBoss Workers

PgBoss replaces Redis and BullMQ.
All async work, scheduling, and retries use PostgreSQL only.

Define queues:

Queue Name	Schedule	Description
purchase-commission	Event-driven	Triggered when purchase completes
daily-commission	Cron: 5 0 * * *	Credit daily SELF / GLOBAL / MONTHLY
eligibility-check	Cron: */10 * * * *	Update leg business + release pending
reconcile-ledger	Cron: 0 1 * * *	Verify ledger vs wallet totals
🔹 Example Worker Registration
import PgBoss from 'pg-boss';
import { CommissionService } from '../modules/commissions/commission.service.js';

const boss = new PgBoss(process.env.DATABASE_URL);
await boss.start();

// Purchase event worker
await boss.work('purchase-commission', async job => {
  const { purchaseId } = job.data;
  await CommissionService.handlePurchase(purchaseId);
});

// Daily cron jobs
await boss.schedule('daily-commission', '5 0 * * *');
await boss.work('daily-commission', async () => {
  await CommissionService.creditDailyCommissions();
});

await boss.schedule('eligibility-check', '*/10 * * * *');
await boss.work('eligibility-check', async () => {
  await CommissionService.recalculateEligibility();
});


✅ Jobs are persistent and resilient —
If the server crashes, PgBoss re-delivers uncompleted jobs automatically.

