🧮 Utility Functions

Implement key helpers:

isUserActive(userId) — Check active purchases.

calculateDailyAmount(monthlyAmount) — monthly / days_in_month.

addLedgerAndWallet(receiverId, sourceId, amount, type, meta) — atomic DB op.

getUplines(userId, depth=9) — Query user_tree_paths.

checkEligibility(userId, level) — Read from level_eligibility.

🔐 Security & Safety

Use JWT authentication for secure routes.

Validate all inputs with Zod.

Always include an idempotency_key on commission inserts.

Use database transactions for wallet updates.

Use Postgres advisory locks for per-user wallet concurrency.

Log every job and worker execution with timestamps.

🧾 Testing

Implement Jest test suites for:

Commission math correctness (daily/monthly)

Purchase flow → wallet updates

Eligibility unlock + pending release

Idempotency (no double credits)

Ledger vs wallet reconciliation

🧠 PgBoss Advantages in This Project

✅ Fully persistent jobs stored in PostgreSQL
✅ Survives crashes and redeploys
✅ No Redis dependency
✅ Supports cron syntax (schedule)
✅ Supports retries and backoff for failed jobs
✅ Perfect for financial systems needing “exactly-once” execution

